id: pm-4v4c
title: Post-install activation verification can load stale overwritten extension modules
description: "Reinstalling an already loaded extension overwrites its files and immediately re-activates it in the same Node process. ESM module caching can retain the prior dependency module namespace, so a newly installed entrypoint importing a newly added named export reports a false activation failure even though the published and installed files are correct; a fresh pm process activates successfully. Reproduced with pm-changelog 2026.7.18: install reported MissingTagHistoryError absent, while tarball/installed release-context.js exported it and package doctor in a fresh process showed activation_status ok."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,cache,extensions,install
created_at: "2026-07-18T12:18:13.064Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T15:37:27.893Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T15:37:27.183Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: Reinstall/upgrade activation verification loads the just-installed module graph rather than stale ESM cache entries; an extension adding a named dependency export upgrades successfully in one process; unchanged extension install and fresh-process doctor behavior remain covered; diagnostics distinguish package defects from verifier cache state.
parent: pm-doxj
risk: medium
confidence: high
